Running command: python - << 'PY'
from pathlib import Path
p = Path('sympy/sympy/logic/boolalg.py')
s = p.read_text()
# find the duplicated block (second occurrence)
first = s.find('\n    def __eq__(self, other):')
second = s.find('\n    def __eq__(self, other):', first+1)
print('first', first, 'second', second)
if second!=-1:
    # find where the duplicated block ends (before '    def _noop')
    end = s.find('\n    def _noop', second)
    if end!=-1:
        new = s[:second] + s[end:]
        p.write_text(new)
        print('removed duplicate')
    else:
        print('end not found')
else:
    print('no duplicate')
PY
